## MEAN STACK DEPLOYMENT TO UBUNTU IN AWS DOCUMENTATION

`sudo apt update`
`sudo apt upgrade`
`sudo apt -y install curl dirmngr apt-transport-https lsb-release ca-certificates`
![certifcates status](./images/certificates%20status.png)
`curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_12.x | sudo -E bash -`
`sudo apt install -y nodejs`
![nodejs status](./images/nodejs%20status.png)
`sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv 0C49F3730359A14518585931BC711F9BA15703C6`
`![sudo apt-key status](./images/sudo%20apt-key%20status.png)
`sudo apt install -y mongodb`
![-y mongodb status](./images/-y%20mongodb%20status.png)
`sudo service mongodb start`
`sudo systemctl status mongodb`
`sudo apt install -y npm`
![npm status](./images/npm%20status.png)
`sudo npm install body-parser`
![body-parser status](./images/body-parser%20status.png)
`mkdir Books && cd Books`
`sudo npm install express mongoose`
![express mongoose status](./images/express%20mongoose%20status.png)
`node server.js`
![web book status](./images/web%20book%20status.png)
